  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Passive from Hollow Verbs (Ajwaf)",
      "titleArabic": "المبني للمجهول من الأجوف",
      "content": [
        "Hollow verbs (ajwaf) - those with wāw or yā' as middle radical - have special passive forms. The weak letter undergoes changes when forming the passive."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Hollow verbs change their middle vowel in passive",
        "قَالَ (to say) → قِيلَ (it was said)",
        "Participles from hollow verbs follow special patterns"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "قَالَ → قِيلَ", "english": "said → was said" },
        { "arabic": "بَاعَ → بِيعَ", "english": "sold → was sold" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Form V Verbs (تَفَعَّلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "باب تَفَعَّلَ",
      "content": [
        "Form V verbs are formed by prefixing تَ to Form II. This pattern often indicates the reflexive of Form II - doing something to oneself or undergoing the action of Form II."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: تَفَعَّلَ (tafa''ala) - prefix tā' to Form II",
        "Maṣdar pattern: تَفَعُّل (tafa''ul)",
        "Reflexive of Form II: عَلَّمَ (to teach) → تَعَلَّمَ (to learn)",
        "Indicates becoming or taking on a quality gradually"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "تَعَلَّمَ", "english": "to learn (reflexive of 'to teach')" },
        { "arabic": "تَكَلَّمَ", "english": "to speak" },
        { "arabic": "تَذَكَّرَ", "english": "to remember" }
      ]
    }
  ],
